  "title": "ParseURL not called on every back or forward button click",
  "body": "## 🐛 Bug description\r\n\r\nparseURL is not called on every back or forward button click.\r\n\r\n## 🔍 Bug reproduction\r\n\r\n**Steps to reproduce the behavior:**\r\n\r\n1. Go to https://codesandbox.io/s/algolia-bad-behaviour-b5ed6\r\n2. Select HP\r\n3. Select Samsung\r\n4. Hit Back button\r\n5. Hit Forward button\r\n6. See in the console that parseURL is not called at each back or forward button blick\r\n\r\n**Live reproduction:**\r\n\r\nIn this sandbox, the url path is mapped to selected brands through parseURL, createURL, stateToRoute and routeToState.\r\n\r\nhttps://codesandbox.io/s/algolia-bad-behaviour-b5ed6\r\n\r\n## 💭 Expected behavior\r\n\r\nI was expecting, as described in your documentation, that parseURL is called on every back or forward button click.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n- OS: Linux, MacOS Windows\r\n- Browser: Chrome, Safari at least\r\n- Version: latest\r\n\r\n## Additional context\r\n\r\nOriginally thought it was a problem of interactions with turbolinks (#2998).\r\n",
